begin
reserve x for set;
reserve R1 for Relation;
reserve R2 for Relation;
theorem
Th10: ( Im (( R1 \/ R2 ),x) ) = ( ( Im (R1,x) ) \/ ( Im (R2,x) ) )
proof
thus ( Im (( R1 \/ R2 ),x) ) c= ( ( Im (R1,x) ) \/ ( Im (R2,x) ) )
proof
let y being set;
assume y in ( Im (( R1 \/ R2 ),x) );
then [ x,y ] in ( R1 \/ R2 ) by CKB10:1;
then ([ x,y ] in R1 or [ x,y ] in R2) by XBOOLE_0:def 3;
then (y in ( Im (R1,x) ) or y in ( Im (R2,x) )) by CKB10:1;
hence thesis by XBOOLE_0:def 3;
end;

let y being set;
assume A1: y in ( ( Im (R1,x) ) \/ ( Im (R2,x) ) );
per cases  by A1,XBOOLE_0:def 3;
suppose y in ( Im (R1,x) );

then [ x,y ] in R1 by CKB10:1;
then [ x,y ] in ( R1 \/ R2 ) by XBOOLE_0:def 3;
hence thesis by CKB10:1;
end;
suppose y in ( Im (R2,x) );

then [ x,y ] in R2 by CKB10:1;
then [ x,y ] in ( R1 \/ R2 ) by XBOOLE_0:def 3;
hence thesis by CKB10:1;
end;
end;
